    ,
    
    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "The following safety measures must be followed for refrigerant R134a and R1234yf (additional regulations may apply in certain countries)."
    ,
    
    
    "If repair work necessitates opening the refrigerant circuit, the refrigerant circuit must first be emptied. Avoid all contact with liquid or gaseous refrigerants. If refrigerant should escape despite all safety measures having been taken, do not inhale the resulting refrigerant/air mixture. Switch on extraction systems, protect hands with rubber gloves and protect eyes with protective goggles."
    ,
    
    
    "If refrigerant gets onto any other body parts despite all safety measures having been taken, these should also be rinsed immediately and thoroughly with water for at least 15 minutes."
    ,
    
    
    "Smoking, welding, soldering and hard-soldering is prohibited in a room containing refrigerant."
    ,
    
    
    "Read the relevant safety data sheet for handling refrigerant R134a and R1234yf."
    ,
    
    
    "The air-conditioning system is pressurised when filled and must not be opened in this state."
    ,
    
    
    "Used or damaged condensers and evaporators must be marked before disposing of them in order to rule out any possibility of them being re-used."
    
    ]
    
    }
    
